Package com.camerontec.catalys.util.fast.template

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IGroup  
    IInstruction
    FAST instruction - this can be a simple typed field (integer, decimal, asciiString, etc), a group, a sequence or a template reference.
    IInstructions
    Collection of FAST instructions.
    INamedInstructions  
    ISequence  
    ITemplate
    A "template" as defined in the FAST spec.
    ITemplateRegistry
    Registry of all templates, accessible by their template identifiers which are assumed to be taken from the id portion of each template name.
    ITemplates  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FastGroup  
    FastInstructions  
    FastNamedInstructions  
    FastSequence  
    FastTemplate  
    FastTemplates  
    LargeIdsTemplateRegistry
    ITemplateRegistry which assumes that templates are registered with discountinuos and possibly large IDs: example (120, 16002, 16003) Compare this to the StandardTemplateRegistry implementation where n templates are stored sequencially in an array with id's 0..n-1.
    StandardTemplateRegistry
    ITemplateRegistry which assumes that templates are registered with sequential int id's starting from 0.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    TemplateException
